<dl id="n20232d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n20" href="#n20232d">N20 (VI.B.13)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n20all.htm#n20232d"> 232(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">X</font> full of eyes / &mdash; &mdash; stains / &mdash; &mdash; holes / &mdash; &mdash; buttons / &mdash; &mdash; medals</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Now as he read John&apos;s <cite>Revelation</cite> new matter was unfolded before him. He perceived that the four mysterious &ldquo;beasts,&rdquo; &ldquo;full of eyes before and behind,&rdquo; &hellip; were not &ldquo;beasts&rdquo; at all; but that the Greek word meant &ldquo;beings,&rdquo; or &ldquo;Living-Ones.&rdquo; He went back to the Four Living Creatures of Ezekiel&apos;s vision (the watercolour drawings he made for Butts, the only buyer of his work, reveal the track of his thoughts) <small> Darrell Figgis, <a name="DFPW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DFPW"><cite title="source">The Paintings of William Blake</cite></a> (1925) 43</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c13024a" href="c13all.htm#c13024a">VI.C.13:024(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
